24template <typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
25constexpr static BitsT Bit(ParamT x)
26{
27 // It's undefined behavior if the shift size is equal to or larger than the width of the type.
28 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(x) < sizeof(BitsT) * 8);
29
30 return (static_cast<BitsT>(1) << static_cast<size_t>(x));
31}
32
33template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT = std::size_t>
34class BitSetT final
35{
36 public:
37 class Reference final
38 {
39 public:
40 ~Reference() {}
41 Reference &operator=(bool x)
42 {
43 mParent->set(mBit, x);
44 return *this;
45 }
46 explicit operator bool() const { return mParent->test(mBit); }
47
48 private:
49 friend class BitSetT;
50
51 Reference(BitSetT *parent, ParamT bit) : mParent(parent), mBit(bit) {}
52
53 BitSetT *mParent;
54 ParamT mBit;
55 };
56
57 class Iterator final
58 {
59 public:
60 Iterator(const BitSetT &bits);
61 Iterator &operator++();
62
63 bool operator==(const Iterator &other) const;
64 bool operator!=(const Iterator &other) const;
65 ParamT operator*() const;
66
67 // These helper functions allow mutating an iterator in-flight.
68 // They only operate on later bits to ensure we don't iterate the same bit twice.
69 void resetLaterBit(std::size_t index)
70 {
71 ASSERT(index > mCurrentBit);
72 mBitsCopy.reset(index);
73 }
74
75 void setLaterBit(std::size_t index)
76 {
77 ASSERT(index > mCurrentBit);
78 mBitsCopy.set(index);
79 }
80
81 private:
82 std::size_t getNextBit();
83
84 BitSetT mBitsCopy;
85 std::size_t mCurrentBit;
86 };
87
88 using value_type = BitsT;
89
90 BitSetT();
91 constexpr explicit BitSetT(BitsT value);
92
93 BitSetT(const BitSetT &other);
94 BitSetT &operator=(const BitSetT &other);
95
96 bool operator==(const BitSetT &other) const;
97 bool operator!=(const BitSetT &other) const;
98
99 constexpr bool operator[](ParamT pos) const;
100 Reference operator[](ParamT pos) { return Reference(this, pos); }
101
102 bool test(ParamT pos) const;
103
104 bool all() const;
105 bool any() const;
106 bool none() const;
107 std::size_t count() const;
108
109 constexpr std::size_t size() const { return N; }
110
111 BitSetT &operator&=(const BitSetT &other);
112 BitSetT &operator|=(const BitSetT &other);
113 BitSetT &operator^=(const BitSetT &other);
114 BitSetT operator~() const;
115
116 BitSetT &operator&=(BitsT value);
117 BitSetT &operator|=(BitsT value);
118 BitSetT &operator^=(BitsT value);
119
120 BitSetT operator<<(std::size_t pos) const;
121 BitSetT &operator<<=(std::size_t pos);
122 BitSetT operator>>(std::size_t pos) const;
123 BitSetT &operator>>=(std::size_t pos);
124
125 BitSetT &set();
126 BitSetT &set(ParamT pos, bool value = true);
127
128 BitSetT &reset();
129 BitSetT &reset(ParamT pos);
130
131 BitSetT &flip();
132 BitSetT &flip(ParamT pos);
133
134 unsigned long to_ulong() const { return static_cast<unsigned long>(mBits); }
135 BitsT bits() const { return mBits; }
136
137 Iterator begin() const { return Iterator(*this); }
138 Iterator end() const { return Iterator(BitSetT()); }
139
140 constexpr static BitSetT Zero() { return BitSetT(); }
141
142 ParamT first() const;
143
144 private:
145 // Produces a mask of ones up to the "x"th bit.
146 constexpr static BitsT Mask(std::size_t x)
147 {
148 return ((Bit<BitsT>(static_cast<ParamT>(x - 1)) - 1) << 1) + 1;
149 }
150
151 BitsT mBits;
152};
153
154template <size_t N>
155class IterableBitSet : public std::bitset<N>
156{
157 public:
158 IterableBitSet() {}
159 IterableBitSet(const std::bitset<N> &implicitBitSet) : std::bitset<N>(implicitBitSet) {}
160
161 class Iterator final
162 {
163 public:
164 Iterator(const std::bitset<N> &bits);
165 Iterator &operator++();
166
167 bool operator==(const Iterator &other) const;
168 bool operator!=(const Iterator &other) const;
169 unsigned long operator*() const { return mCurrentBit; }
170
171 // These helper functions allow mutating an iterator in-flight.
172 // They only operate on later bits to ensure we don't iterate the same bit twice.
173 void resetLaterBit(std::size_t index)
174 {
175 ASSERT(index > mCurrentBit);
176 mBits.reset(index - mOffset);
177 }
178
179 void setLaterBit(std::size_t index)
180 {
181 ASSERT(index > mCurrentBit);
182 mBits.set(index - mOffset);
183 }
184
185 private:
186 unsigned long getNextBit();
187
188 static constexpr size_t BitsPerWord = sizeof(uint32_t) * 8;
189 std::bitset<N> mBits;
190 unsigned long mCurrentBit;
191 unsigned long mOffset;
192 };
193
194 Iterator begin() const { return Iterator(*this); }
195 Iterator end() const { return Iterator(std::bitset<N>(0)); }
196};
197
198template <size_t N>
199IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator::Iterator(const std::bitset<N> &bitset)
200 : mBits(bitset), mCurrentBit(0), mOffset(0)
201{
202 if (mBits.any())
203 {
204 mCurrentBit = getNextBit();
205 }
206 else
207 {
208 mOffset = static_cast<unsigned long>(rx::roundUpPow2(N, BitsPerWord));
209 }
210}
211
212template <size_t N>
213ANGLE_INLINE typename IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator &IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator::operator++()
214{
215 ASSERT(mBits.any());
216 mBits.set(mCurrentBit - mOffset, 0);
217 mCurrentBit = getNextBit();
218 return *this;
219}
220
221template <size_t N>
222bool IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator::operator==(const Iterator &other) const
223{
224 return mOffset == other.mOffset && mBits == other.mBits;
225}
226
227template <size_t N>
228bool IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator::operator!=(const Iterator &other) const
229{
230 return !(*this == other);
231}
232
233template <size_t N>
234unsigned long IterableBitSet<N>::Iterator::getNextBit()
235{
236 // TODO(jmadill): Use 64-bit scan when possible.
237 static constexpr std::bitset<N> wordMask(std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
238
239 while (mOffset < N)
240 {
241 uint32_t wordBits = static_cast<uint32_t>((mBits & wordMask).to_ulong());
242 if (wordBits != 0)
243 {
244 return gl::ScanForward(wordBits) + mOffset;
245 }
246
247 mBits >>= BitsPerWord;
248 mOffset += BitsPerWord;
249 }
250 return 0;
251}
252
253template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
254BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::BitSetT() : mBits(0)
255{
256 static_assert(N > 0, "Bitset type cannot support zero bits.");
257 static_assert(N <= sizeof(BitsT) * 8, "Bitset type cannot support a size this large.");
258}
259
260template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
261constexpr BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::BitSetT(BitsT value) : mBits(value & Mask(N))
262{}
263
264template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
265BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::BitSetT(const BitSetT &other) : mBits(other.mBits)
266{}
267
268template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
269BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator=(const BitSetT &other)
270{
271 mBits = other.mBits;
272 return *this;
273}
274
275template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
276bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator==(const BitSetT &other) const
277{
278 return mBits == other.mBits;
279}
280
281template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
282bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator!=(const BitSetT &other) const
283{
284 return mBits != other.mBits;
285}
286
287template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
288constexpr bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator[](ParamT pos) const
289{
290 return test(pos);
291}
292
293template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
294bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::test(ParamT pos) const
295{
296 return (mBits & Bit<BitsT>(pos)) != 0;
297}
298
299template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
300bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::all() const
301{
302 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
303 return mBits == Mask(N);
304}
305
306template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
307bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::any() const
308{
309 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
310 return (mBits != 0);
311}
312
313template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
314bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::none() const
315{
316 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
317 return (mBits == 0);
318}
319
320template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
321std::size_t BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::count() const
322{
323 return gl::BitCount(mBits);
324}
325
326template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
327BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator&=(const BitSetT &other)
328{
329 mBits &= other.mBits;
330 return *this;
331}
332
333template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
334BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator|=(const BitSetT &other)
335{
336 mBits |= other.mBits;
337 return *this;
338}
339
340template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
341BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator^=(const BitSetT &other)
342{
343 mBits = mBits ^ other.mBits;
344 return *this;
345}
346
347template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
348BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator~() const
349{
350 return BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>(~mBits & Mask(N));
351}
352
353template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
354BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator&=(BitsT value)
355{
356 mBits &= value;
357 return *this;
358}
359
360template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
361BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator|=(BitsT value)
362{
363 mBits |= value & Mask(N);
364 return *this;
365}
366
367template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
368BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator^=(BitsT value)
369{
370 mBits ^= value & Mask(N);
371 return *this;
372}
373
374template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
375BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator<<(std::size_t pos) const
376{
377 return BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>((mBits << pos) & Mask(N));
378}
379
380template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
381BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator<<=(std::size_t pos)
382{
383 mBits = (mBits << pos & Mask(N));
384 return *this;
385}
386
387template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
388BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator>>(std::size_t pos) const
389{
390 return BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>(mBits >> pos);
391}
392
393template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
394BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::operator>>=(std::size_t pos)
395{
396 mBits = ((mBits >> pos) & Mask(N));
397 return *this;
398}
399
400template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
401BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::set()
402{
403 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
404 mBits = Mask(N);
405 return *this;
406}
407
408template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
409BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::set(ParamT pos, bool value)
410{
411 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
412 if (value)
413 {
414 mBits |= Bit<BitsT>(pos) & Mask(N);
415 }
416 else
417 {
418 reset(pos);
419 }
420 return *this;
421}
422
423template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
424BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::reset()
425{
426 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
427 mBits = 0;
428 return *this;
429}
430
431template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
432BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::reset(ParamT pos)
433{
434 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
435 mBits &= ~Bit<BitsT>(pos);
436 return *this;
437}
438
439template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
440BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::flip()
441{
442 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
443 mBits ^= Mask(N);
444 return *this;
445}
446
447template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
448BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::flip(ParamT pos)
449{
450 ASSERT(mBits == (mBits & Mask(N)));
451 mBits ^= Bit<BitsT>(pos) & Mask(N);
452 return *this;
453}
454
455template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
456ParamT BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::first() const
457{
458 ASSERT(!none());
459 return static_cast<ParamT>(gl::ScanForward(mBits));
460}
461
462template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
463BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::Iterator(const BitSetT &bits) : mBitsCopy(bits), mCurrentBit(0)
464{
465 if (bits.any())
466 {
467 mCurrentBit = getNextBit();
468 }
469}
470
471template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
472ANGLE_INLINE typename BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator &
473BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::operator++()
474{
475 ASSERT(mBitsCopy.any());
476 mBitsCopy.reset(static_cast<ParamT>(mCurrentBit));
477 mCurrentBit = getNextBit();
478 return *this;
479}
480
481template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
482bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::operator==(const Iterator &other) const
483{
484 return mBitsCopy == other.mBitsCopy;
485}
486
487template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
488bool BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::operator!=(const Iterator &other) const
489{
490 return !(*this == other);
491}
492
493template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
494ParamT BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::operator*() const
495{
496 return static_cast<ParamT>(mCurrentBit);
497}
498
499template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
500std::size_t BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT>::Iterator::getNextBit()
501{
502 if (mBitsCopy.none())
503 {
504 return 0;
505 }
506
507 return gl::ScanForward(mBitsCopy.mBits);
508}

510template <size_t N>
511using BitSet8 = BitSetT<N, uint8_t>;
512
513template <size_t N>
514using BitSet16 = BitSetT<N, uint16_t>;
515
516template <size_t N>
517using BitSet32 = BitSetT<N, uint32_t>;
518
519template <size_t N>
520using BitSet64 = BitSetT<N, uint64_t>;

522namespace priv
523{
524
525template <size_t N, typename T>
526using EnableIfBitsFit = typename std::enable_if<N <= sizeof(T) * 8>::type;
527
528template <size_t N, typename Enable = void>
529struct GetBitSet
530{
531 using Type = IterableBitSet<N>;
532};
533
534// Prefer 64-bit bitsets on 64-bit CPUs. They seem faster than 32-bit.
535#if defined(ANGLE_IS_64_BIT_CPU)
536template <size_t N>
537struct GetBitSet<N, EnableIfBitsFit<N, uint64_t>>
538{
539 using Type = BitSet64<N>;
540};
541#else
542template <size_t N>
543struct GetBitSet<N, EnableIfBitsFit<N, uint32_t>>
544{
545 using Type = BitSet32<N>;
546};
547#endif // defined(ANGLE_IS_64_BIT_CPU)
548
549} // namespace priv
550
551template <size_t N>
552using BitSet = typename priv::GetBitSet<N>::Type;
553
554} // namespace angle
555
556template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
557inline angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> operator&(const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &lhs,
558 const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &rhs)
559{
560 angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> result(lhs);
561 result &= rhs.bits();
562 return result;
563}
564
565template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
566inline angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> operator|(const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &lhs,
567 const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &rhs)
568{
569 angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> result(lhs);
570 result |= rhs.bits();
571 return result;
572}
573
574template <size_t N, typename BitsT, typename ParamT>
575inline angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> operator^(const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &lhs,
576 const angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> &rhs)
577{
578 angle::BitSetT<N, BitsT, ParamT> result(lhs);
579 result ^= rhs.bits();
580 return result;
581}
